6.5 Assume Breach: The Modern Defensive Mindset
"Assume Breach" is not defeatism—it is strategic realism. It acknowledges that:
1. Perfect prevention is impossible given attacker advantages and business constraints
2. Detection and response are force multipliers that reduce attacker ROI
3. Lateral movement is the killer—initial compromise is inevitable; domain takeover is not
Architectural implications:
•  Zero Trust: Verify every access request, regardless of network location
•  Micro-segmentation: Isolate workloads so compromise of one doesn't threaten all
•  Privileged Access Management (PAM): Protect the "keys to the kingdom" with extreme prejudice
•  Comprehensive telemetry: You cannot detect what you cannot see
