8.2 Base64: The Attacker's Friend
Base64 encodes binary data as ASCII, evading simple string matching:
Encoding process:
1. Binary data → 6-bit groups → ASCII characters (A-Z, a-z, 0-9, +, /, =)
Why attackers use it:
•  Bypasses signature detection looking for binary patterns
•  Safe for transmission in text protocols (HTTP, email)
•  Native support in PowerShell, Python, JavaScript
•  Looks "random" to casual inspection
SOC analyst skill: Recognize Base64 patterns (length divisible by 4, character set, padding =). Decode suspicious strings:
