In Chapter 3: Networking Fundamentals, we extend our understanding from single-system internals to the digital arteries connecting them. You will learn how data travels across the wire, how protocols can be abused for covert channels, and why network telemetry remains the defender's most reliable visibility source—even as encryption increasingly obscures content.
The network is where an attacker's footprints are hardest to erase. While they can delete logs on a compromised host, they cannot hide the physical act of transmitting packets across infrastructure they do not control. Understanding networking is understanding the hunt.
